	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=17094><span id=Sage>Kneesmasher</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>397 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.81]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>My oh my, what a dilema. Once again confusion over 1-hs weapons and 2-hs weapons. Why must so many players think they can only choose one? I don't get it...I currently carry THREE different weapon combinations with me at ALL TIMES and use each according to the situation.<br><br>Your mithril 2-hs is a nice weapon. The haste is what makes it so. Keep it. You are only level 33 but obviously have a LOT of resources at your disposal so just keep it, unless you have some other Uber haste item...(more later)<br><br>The only question you raise is whether to use a Skyfire or a Wurmslayer. Since both of those weapons are WAY beyond most level 33 players, you can't go wrong with either. It would simply be a matter of preference, nothing more.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Wurm is very heavy and in protracted battles it can cause problems with Stamina. It is slow when compared to the Skyfire. It hits hard though with a damage of 25.  The Skyfire is fast and nimble with a nice proc. You will not have stamina problems with Skyfire but will have to get over hitting for 70pts a shot. Skyfire will not even proc for you at level 33 and won't for many levels to come if my memory serves me right. So you would only be looking at the melee damage it can do. And when it does proc, you will take damage from the proc as well....just something to consider. Many people call it the Suicide Sword.<br><br>If you have an FBSS (and since you have all these Uber weapons at your disposal, why not have an FBSS too!) then the question becomes the haste's stackability with the weapons. I do not believe (correct me if I'm wrong) that the FBSS haste stacks with the Mithril 2-hs haste.  But still, the Mithril 2-hs will give an equivalent delay of approximately 31. Not bad for a 2-hs.  With the Wurm, the haste will work which can lead to awesome damage, but will zap your stamina in short order. Stamina drain is not really a problem when grouped, but solo can be a pain.  It should also stack with the Skyfire which will lead to a flurry of attacks where you nickle and dime the mob to death and sounds like it would be lots of fun to wield. <br><br>If you REALLY must make a choice, my advice would be go out solo, pick a common blue mob that is pretty standard in levels, like the Tesch Mas Gnolls in South Karana, fight it repeatedly (30-40 times) using the different weapon combinations equally, and see which one you think does best. Keep that one.<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>45th Circle of Dwarven Paladins<br>Twilight Brethren<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"</p>&nbsp;<br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"</td></td></tr>
